    <subfield code="a">Correspondence arising from the Bishop&apos;s pastoral letter of 28 April, 1862, in which the character of General Thomas Evans was &quot;assailed&quot;. General Evans had offered to assist the financing of a new church on Sherbrooke St., Montreal, of which his son-in-law, Isaac Hellmuth, would be rector. This incident was brought out by the Bishop in the course of a polemical exchange with Hellmuth.</subfield>
